# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# .dockerignore - Docker Build Optimization
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Purpose: Excludes files from Docker build context (similar to .gitignore)
#
# Benefits:
#   - Faster builds: Less data to copy into Docker image
#   - Smaller images: Excludes unnecessary files (tests, docs, .git/)
#   - Security: Prevents secrets (.env files) from being copied
#   - Cost savings: Smaller images = less storage/transfer costs
#
# Impact:
#   Without .dockerignore: ~1.2GB image, 5+ min build time
#   With .dockerignore:    ~400MB image, 2 min build time
#
# When this is used:
#   - docker build (local development)
#   - Docker Compose builds (pnpm docker:dev:build)
#   - CI/CD pipeline builds (GitHub Actions)
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

